s.text: In the preamble, HUD states that no further review is necessary.

HUD states that the interim rule will not have a substantial, direct effect on the States or on the relationship between the federal government and the States or on the distribution of power or responsibilities among various levels of government because the interim rule primarily involves relationships between HUD and private entities.
In the preamble to the rule, HUD states that it may not conduct or sponsor and a person is not required to respond to a collection of information until OMB has issued the control number.

Pursuant to section 801(a)(2)(A) of title 5, United States Code, this is our report on a major rule promulgated by the Department of Housing and Urban Development (HUD), entitled "Single Family Mortgage Insurance; Loss Mitigation Procedures" (RIN: 2502-AG72).
